⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Defenders of Naju
node TGL · TGL · ⟦The Defenders of Naju:TGL:d6e63f⟧

WHO   — The Defenders of Naju — the alien guardians
WHAT  — The hostile, living menace of the invading world — the beasts and guardians that hold Naju's Corridors and depths, standing between the Guardian and the self-destruct she has come to arm.
WHERE — TGL · The Guardian Legend  Framework inputs: The Guardian Legend (Compile, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Naju falls toward Earth and something must hold its halls; because a world full of monsters does not yield its heart willingly; because every door to the self-destruct is a thing that must be beaten before it will open.
HOW   — By guarding — one boss at the end of each of the ten Corridors, and the creatures that fill the depths between — barring the Guardian's path until each is defeated in turn and the way to the self-destruct is clear.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We are the menace of Naju — we hold every door, and the Guardian must pass through us or not at all.

